  "description": "A dramatic, close-up view of El Capitan in Yosemite National Park, framed by dark green pine branches in the foreground. The massive granite monolith dominates the scene, its textured face showing layers of rock and subtle shading. Mist or low clouds cling to the upper reaches of the formation, enhancing its imposing scale. The lighting suggests either early morning or late afternoon, casting shadows that accentuate the rock's contours. The foreground branches add depth and a natural framing element, while the sky above appears soft and diffused.",
